n <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../181/506181.xml">
filmmaker</link>.<p>

Ngakane was educated at <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../996/65996.xml">
Fort Hare University College</link> and <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../467/320467.xml">
Wits University</link>, and worked on <it><link>
 Drum</link></it> and <it><link>
Zonk</link></it> magazines from 1948 to 1950. In 1950 he began his career in film as an assistant director and actor in the film version of <it><movie wordnetid="106613686" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../462/10476462.xml">
Cry, the Beloved Country</link></movie>
</it>, directed by <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../589/2816589.xml">
Zoltan Korda</link>. Shortly thereafter he went into exile in the <autocracy wordnetid="108361001" confidence="0.8">
<system wordnetid="108435388" confidence="0.8">
